reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent product but not sure if I would pay $100
reviews.reviewText: This is a decent console table but I definitely wouldn't pay $100 for it, as Amazon better console tables for the same price (they're bigger and have better features). Tables measurements match what's shown on Amazon at 31.9"H x 35.4"W x 11.8"D. I like the look of the solid black finish, as it goes with my other living room furniture. It states that it has a waterproof finish, which is also accurate but that's also not the greatest thing either, as you can see in the picture showing how well the waterproof finish works, it also shows all the fingerprints. The 2 drawers are NOT wood/fake wood/particleboard, whatever you want to call it but fabric drawers. I don't know why they decided to go this route when Amazon has other console tables that are the same price or cheaper but are bigger size with better features. Even though I'm not very happy about the fabric drawers, at the very least they are a solid fabric drawer if anything else.... I just wish they were bigger because we plan on putting our printer on this table and I wanted to put the toner in the drawers but they don't fit because the drawers are to small.It does say 2 person assembly in the instructions but my husband was able to put this together by himself without any difficulty and within 30 minutes or less. Overall, I like the solid black finish but don't like how easily fingerprint show up, even though it's waterproof. I also wish the fabric drawers were bigger and made of the same material as the rest of the table (not fabric).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent but Chips Easily
reviews.reviewText: So here we goPros:+ metal construction for legs which seems really durable and pretty stylish+ easy assembly, each screw has an anchor to go into so you can never overtighten and damage it.+Cons:- VERY easily damaged, the tops arrived Pristine as far as I could tell but despite handling it with kid gloves and assembling it on the carpet two chips appeared in very noticable areas, I have no idea how they could have happend I was incredbly gentle with the thing.- The metal while sturdy is also easily scuffed and white marks appear easily- The drawers are made of a cheap disposable kind of material although the front is pleathered to appear nicer.End verdict for now, I like it, I hate that thing chips so easy and if I paid the asking price of $80 (currently on sale from $100) I'd probably be a little miffed.That said so far its a pretty good piece of furnature I'll update as time goes on
